### Backend Execution Model
Resolvers compile values for schema fields. They receive four parameters:
- `parent`: Result of the parent resolver.
- `args`: Parameters passed in query (e.g. `id`).
- `context`: Shared request state (e.g., current user, DB connections).
- `info`: AST query parameters.
