### proxy_pass Configuration
Route incoming traffic to application servers running locally:
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name api.mysite.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:8080;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    }
}
```

### Distributing Traffic
Configure upstream blocks to distribute workloads across a cluster of server nodes:
```nginx
upstream backend_servers {
    least_conn; # Upstream algorithm choice
    server 10.0.0.10:8080;
    server 10.0.0.11:8080;
}
server {
    listen 80;
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend_servers;
    }
}
```

### Securing Connections (Port 443)
Configure SSL keys and automatically redirect HTTP requests to HTTPS:
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name mysite.com;
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri; # Redirect rule
}
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name mysite.com;

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/mysite.com/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/mysite.com/privkey.pem;
}
```

### Restricting Abusive Clients
- **Rate Limiting**: Deny requests exceeding access thresholds:
  ```nginx
  limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=mylimit:10m rate=10r/s;
  server {
      location /login {
          limit_req zone=mylimit burst=5 nodelay;
      }
  }
  ```
- **Secure Headers**: Append headers to prevent XSS and clickjacking: `add_header X-Frame-Options DENY;`.
